-- Algebra/representation_bound.math
--
-- The box bound for positive-definite integer forms — the negative side
-- of the bounded representation check (fifteen-theorem stage S3.T1).
-- Every vector where the form takes the value `target` lies in the
-- explicit finite box
--
--   det(A) · x(i)² ≤ adj(A)(i,i) · target,
--
-- and any vector outside that box takes a value exceeding `target`, so
-- deciding `Represents(A, target)` is a finite search. The engine is the
-- Cauchy–Schwarz inequality for the A-pairing, evaluated at the integral
-- vector adj(A)·e_i, whose A-pairing with x is det(A)·x(i).

module Algebra.representation_bound

